def ismostlymagicsquare(a):
    g=0
    apple=[]
    kashmir=[]
    k=0
    row=len(a)
    col=len(a[0])
    if row==col:
        for i in range(0,row):
            g+=a[i][i]
            k+=a[i][row-i-1]
            d=0
            b=0
            for j in range(0,col):
                d+=a[i][j]                
                b+=a[j][i]
            kashmir.append(b)
            apple.append(d)
            kashmir=list(set(kashmir))
            apple=list(set(apple))
            if len(kashmir)==len(apple)==1 and kashmir[0]==apple[0]==g==k:
                return True
    return False
